&lt;p&gt;Let's play with cookies. The following form makes a little scratch-pad type dealie using a cookie to store the text. Hitting 'save' stores the text you type into a field in the cookie named 'text'. Hitting 'load' takes the text (if any) from your cookie and puts it in the textarea.
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;
Of course, it'll only hang around as long as your cookie does...! &lt;del&gt;Annoyingly, mozilla doesn't seem to like it so far, but IE does. Grr.&lt;/del&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;form name=&quot;cookieForm&quot; action=&quot;javascript: doccument.location = document.location&quot;&gt;
&lt;script&gt;

function saveCookie(name, text) {
  document.cookie = (name+&quot;=&quot;+escape(text)+&quot;;&quot;+document.cookie);
}

function loadCookie(name) {
  var text=document.cookie;
  if (text.indexOf(name+&quot;=&quot;) == -1) text=&quot;&quot;;
  text=text.substr(text.indexOf(name+&quot;=&quot;)+name.length+1);
  if (text.indexOf(&quot;;&quot;) != -1)
    text=text.substr(0, text.indexOf(&quot;;&quot;));
  return unescape(text);
}

&lt;/script&gt;
&lt;table&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;
&lt;textarea rows=20 cols=60 name=text&gt;
&lt;/textarea&gt;

&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;

&lt;input type=submit value=&quot;count&quot;
  onClick=&quot;alert(cookieForm.text.value.length+' chars')&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;

&lt;input type=submit value=&quot;save&quot;
  onClick=&quot;saveCookie('text', cookieForm.text.value)&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;input type=submit value=&quot;load&quot;
  onClick=&quot;cookieForm.text.value=loadCookie('text')&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;

&lt;input type=submit value=&quot;show&quot;
  onClick=&quot;alert(document.cookie)&quot;&gt;

&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/form&gt;

&lt;script&gt;
cookieForm.text.value=loadCookie('text');
&lt;/script&gt;


